Installation

To install, copy the content of "bin" folder to desired location.

Software was tested under Perl 5.10.

Perl scripts are configure with "/usr/bin/perl".
The following CPAN Perl modules are required:
* Parallel::ForkManager

Path to NCBI "blastn" executable is expected in shell PATH. 
Alternatively, path to “blastn” can be set directly in "gm_hm.pl" script 
by modifying the line 
    my $blastn = "blastn";


Download and install database model files and pangenome sequence
cd bin
wget https://genemark-hm.s3.amazonaws.com/refmod.tar.gz
tar xf refmod.tar.gz

mkdir refdb
cd refdb
wget https://genemark-hm.s3.amazonaws.com/pan.fasta
makeblastdb -in pan.fasta  -parse_seqids -dbtype nucl  -out pan -title pan


Pipeline is ready for execution.

